## Proposed design

### Layer 1 — `src/lib/manifest-mock.ts`
Add a new `generateSoulStream(prompt, name, tier, masterKey, model, signal)` async generator function that yields `ManifestStreamEvent` objects:

```typescript
export type ManifestStreamEvent =
  | { type: "preamble"; content: string }  // the # SOUL.md header (sent first)
  | { type: "chunk"; delta: string }         // each SSE delta
  | { type: "complete"; result: ManifestResult }  // final result
  | { type: "error"; error: string };
```

Implementation:
- If `masterKey` is empty (template fallback): yield the full template as one `chunk` event, then yield `complete` with metrics
- If `masterKey` is set: call `fetch(URL, { ..., signal })` with `stream: true` in the body. Parse SSE chunks via a custom parser (split on `\n\n`, extract `data: ...` lines, JSON.parse each non-`[DONE]` line, yield `delta.choices[0].delta.content`). On stream end, compute final metrics (computeMetrics, calculateSoulHash), yield `complete`
- On network/HTTP error: yield `error` with the error message
- On abort: just stop yielding (don't yield error — abort is user-initiated, not an error)

### Layer 2 — `src/lib/mock-ipc.ts`
Add a new `manifest_soul_stream` command that returns a handle:

```typescript
type StreamHandle = AsyncIterable<ManifestStreamEvent> & {
  cancel: () => void;
};

const activeStreams = new Map<string, AbortController>();

case "manifest_soul_stream": {
  const payload = args as ...;
  const streamId = String(payload._streamId ?? crypto.randomUUID());
  const controller = new AbortController();
  activeStreams.set(streamId, controller);
  return {
    cancel: () => { controller.abort(); activeStreams.delete(streamId); },
    [Symbol.asyncIterator]() {
      return generateSoulStream(..., controller.signal);
    },
  };
}
```

The `cancel_manifest_stream` IPC command is unnecessary because the handle's `cancel()` is held by the renderer.

