OpenRouter free models aggressively cache near-identical prompts. A small `[variant #1]` suffix is unlikely to bust the cache. More reliable approaches:

- Vary temperature (`SOUL_TEMPERATURE + 0.05 * N`, capped at 1.0)
- Pass a `seed` param (OpenRouter supports it on some models; not free tier)
- Perturb the system prompt with a nonce

This is a best-effort attempt; document it as such in the FID or switch to temperature variation.

**`computeSectionMetrics` regex is overly strict:**

`/^(##\s+\d+\.\s+.+)$/gm` requires `## N. Title` (digit + dot + space). Real LLM output often uses:

- `## 1) Title` (parenthesis)
- `## 1 Title` (no dot)
- `## Section 1 — Title` (label + em-dash)

These would all be missed (the fallback `out.length + 1` for id handles malformed headers, but they still get classified as malformed). Consider a more lenient regex like `/^(##\s+(?:\d+[.)]\s*)?.+)$/gm` with the `id` extraction as a best-effort.

